Key Match Events: Franz Wagner led Orlando with a standout 27-point performance, including 17 points in the first quarter.
Goga Bitadze recorded 11 points, nine rebounds (five of which were offensive), three assists, two blocks, and a steal, shooting an efficient 5-for-6 from the field.
Post-Match Reflections: Franz Wagner commended Goga Bitadze’s readiness and defensive effort amid Wendell Carter Jr.'s absence.
Magic head coach Jamahl Mosley praised Bitadze’s defensive impact and his ability to facilitate offense through smart play.
